</p>
<p> During the discussions, it was noted that, although all the countries have 
constitutional and legal frameworks guaranteeing the independence of the judiciary through 
objective and transparent selection, appointment or election procedures, such procedures 
leave room for external and internal interference to varying degrees.  
</p>
<p> </p>

